1.51.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#1432)

Increments the strong reference count on the `Arc<T>` associated with the provided pointer by one.

##### [¬ß](#safety-2)Safety

The pointer must have been obtained through `Arc::into_raw`, and the associated `Arc` instance must be valid (i.e. the strong count must be at least 1) for the duration of this method.

##### [¬ß](#examples-22)Examples

```
use std::sync::Arc;

let five = Arc::new(5);

unsafe {
    let ptr = Arc::into_raw(five);
    Arc::increment_strong_count(ptr);

    // This assertion is deterministic because we haven't shared
    // the `Arc` between threads.
    let five = Arc::from_raw(ptr);
    assert_eq!(2, Arc::strong_count(&five));
}
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::sync::Arc;%0A++++%0A++++let+five+=+Arc::new(5);%0A++++%0A++++unsafe+%7B%0A++++++++let+ptr+=+Arc::into_raw(five);%0A++++++++Arc::increment_strong_count(ptr);%0A++++%0A++++++++//+This+assertion+is+deterministic+because+we+haven%27t+shared%0A++++++++//+the+%60Arc%60+between+threads.%0A++++++++let+five+=+Arc::from_raw(ptr);%0A++++++++assert_eq!(2,+Arc::strong_count(%26five));%0A++++%7D%0A%7D&edition=2021)

1.51.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#1468)

Decrements the strong reference count on the `Arc<T>` associated with the provided pointer by one.

##### [¬ß](#safety-3)Safety

The pointer must have been obtained through `Arc::into_raw`, and the associated `Arc` instance must be valid (i.e. the strong count must be at least 1) when invoking this method. This method can be used to release the final `Arc` and backing storage, but **should not** be called after the final `Arc` has been released.

##### [¬ß](#examples-23)Examples

```
use std::sync::Arc;

let five = Arc::new(5);

unsafe {
    let ptr = Arc::into_raw(five);
    Arc::increment_strong_count(ptr);

    // Those assertions are deterministic because we haven't shared
    // the `Arc` between threads.
    let five = Arc::from_raw(ptr);
    assert_eq!(2, Arc::strong_count(&five));
    Arc::decrement_strong_count(ptr);
    assert_eq!(1, Arc::strong_count(&five));
}
```

