[source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#2459)[¬ß](#method.drop)

Drops the `Arc`.

This will decrement the strong reference count. If the strong reference count reaches zero then the only other references (if any) are [`Weak`](struct.Weak.html "struct std::sync::Weak"), so we `drop` the inner value.

##### [¬ß](#examples-44)Examples

```
use std::sync::Arc;

struct Foo;

impl Drop for Foo {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        println!("dropped!");
    }
}

let foo  = Arc::new(Foo);
let foo2 = Arc::clone(&foo);

drop(foo);    // Doesn't print anything
drop(foo2);   // Prints "dropped!"
```

