1.37.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#3686)[¬ß](#impl-FromIterator%3CT%3E-for-Arc%3C%5BT%5D%3E)

[source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/sync.rs.html#3725)[¬ß](#method.from_iter)

Takes each element in the `Iterator` and collects it into an `Arc<[T]>`.

##### [¬ß](#performance-characteristics)Performance characteristics

###### [¬ß](#the-general-case)The general case

In the general case, collecting into `Arc<[T]>` is done by first collecting into a `Vec<T>`. That is, when writing the following:

```
let evens: Arc<[u8]> = (0..10).filter(|&x| x % 2 == 0).collect();
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::sync::Arc;%0A++++let+evens:+Arc%3C%5Bu8%5D%3E+=+(0..10).filter(%7C%26x%7C+x+%25+2+==+0).collect();%0A++++assert_eq!(%26*evens,+%26%5B0,+2,+4,+6,+8%5D);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

this behaves as if we wrote:

```
let evens: Arc<[u8]> = (0..10).filter(|&x| x % 2 == 0)
    .collect::<Vec<_>>() // The first set of allocations happens here.
    .into(); // A second allocation for `Arc<[T]>` happens here.
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::sync::Arc;%0A++++let+evens:+Arc%3C%5Bu8%5D%3E+=+(0..10).filter(%7C%26x%7C+x+%25+2+==+0)%0A++++++++.collect::%3CVec%3C_%3E%3E()+//+The+first+set+of+allocations+happens+here.%0A++++++++.into();+//+A+second+allocation+for+%60Arc%3C%5BT%5D%3E%60+happens+here.%0A++++assert_eq!(%26*evens,+%26%5B0,+2,+4,+6,+8%5D);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

This will allocate as many times as needed for constructing the `Vec<T>` and then it will allocate once for turning the `Vec<T>` into the `Arc<[T]>`.

###### [¬ß](#iterators-of-known-length)Iterators of known length

When your `Iterator` implements `TrustedLen` and is of an exact size, a single allocation will be made for the `Arc<[T]>`. For example:

```
let evens: Arc<[u8]> = (0..10).collect(); // Just a single allocation happens here.
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::sync::Arc;%0A++++let+evens:+Arc%3C%5Bu8%5D%3E+=+(0..10).collect();+//+Just+a+single+allocation+happens+here.%0A++++assert_eq!(%26*evens,+%26*(0..10).collect::%3CVec%3C_%3E%3E());%0A%7D&edition=2021)

